The paper deals with a problem of lossy source coding with privacy constraints, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of polar codes, which are a type of error-correcting codes, so cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible category. The problem of lossy compression with privacy constraints is relevant in multimedia applications, so cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the tradeoff between utility and privacy, which is a topic in social and information sciences, so cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely but still possible category.
